This paper deals with hyperspectral image processing, which involves analyzing images with a large number of spectral bands. The paper proposes a novel nonlinear spectral unmixing method based on a multilinear mixing model. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories, which often deal with image processing and analysis. The paper also involves optimization and constraint-based methods, which are common in the machine learning (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates and compares the proposed method with existing methods using synthetic and real data sets, indicating that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
